'''Christian Overgaard Nielsen''' (January 16, 1918 – January 26, 1999) was a [[Denmark|Danish]] [[zoologist]] and [[ecologist]].
== Career ==
Overgaard Nielsen was a soil [[ecologist]], specializing in soil [[nematode]]s and [[Enchytraeidae]]. He investigated the role of the soil microfauna in the [[decomposition]] of plant litter and recycling of [[nutrient]]s in [[ecosystem]]s.
He was a visiting scientist with [[Charles Sutherland Elton|Charles Elton]] at [[Oxford University]] in 1950-1953.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=6C4b1nZfrUwC Crowcroft, Peter (1991) Elton's Ecologists: A History of the Bureau of Animal Population. University of Chicago Press] {{ISBN|0-226-12148-8}}</ref> He was then employed at the [[Mols Laboratory]] under [[Aarhus University]]. In 1964, he was appointed professor of [[zoology]] at the [[University of Copenhagen]].<ref>Christensen, B. (2000) ''Christian Overgaard Nielsen 16. januar 1918 - 26. januar 1999''. [[Kongelige Danske Videnskabernes Selskab]] - Oversigt over Selskabets Virksomhed 1998-2000: pp. 352-357.</ref>
He was the first Editor-in-Chief of the scientific journal [[Oikos (journal)|Oikos]] (1949-1965).
