This glossary describes the terms used in formal descriptions of [[spider]]s; where applicable these terms are used in describing other [[arachnid]]s.
{{Compact ToC|pre1=Terms|custom1=Abbreviations|custom2=See also|custom3=References|custom4=Bibliography}}
==Terms== ===A=== [[File:Spider external anatomy main en.png|thumb|upright=1.5|The underside and head of a female ecribellate entelegyne spider]] {{anchor|abdomen}}{{anchor|opisthosoma}}'''Abdomen''' or '''opisthosoma''': One of the two main body parts ([[tagma (biology)|tagmata]]), located towards the [[Posterior (anatomy)|posterior]] end; see also [[Abdomen#Other animals|Abdomen: Other animals]]
{{anchor|anal tubercle}}'''Anal tubercle''': A small protuberance (tubercule) above the ''[[#spinneret|spinnerets]]'' through which the [[anus]] opens{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=13}}
{{anchor|apophysis}}'''Apophysis''' (plural apophyses): An outgrowth or process changing the general shape of a body part, particularly the appendages; often used in describing the male ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalp]]''{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=13}}
{{anchor|atrium}}'''Atrium''' (plural atria): An internal chamber at the entrance to the ''[[#copulation duct|copulation duct]]'' in female [[Haplogynae|haplogyne]] spiders{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=13}}
===B=== {{anchor|bidentate}}'''Bidentate''': Having two teeth
{{anchor|book lungs}}'''Book lungs''': Respiratory organs on the ventral side (underside) of the ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]'', in front of the ''[[#epigastric furrow|epigastric furrow]]'', opening through narrow slits;{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=14}} see also [[Book lung]]s
Bulbus → ''[[#palpal bulb|palpal bulb]]''
===C=== {{anchor|calamistrum}}'''Calamistrum''' (plural calamistra): Modified setae (bristles) on the ''[[#metatarsus|metatarsus]]'' of the fourth leg of spiders with a ''[[#cribellum|cribellum]]'', arranged in one or more rows or in an oval shape, used to comb silk produced by the cribellum; see also [[Calamistrum]]
Caput (plural capita): → ''[[#cephalic region|cephalic region]]''
{{anchor|carapace}}'''Carapace''': A hardened plate (sclerite) covering the upper (dorsal) portion of the ''[[#cephalothorax|cephalothorax]]'';{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=14}} see also [[Carapace]]
{{anchor|carpoblem}}'''Carpoblem''': The principal ''[[#tibia|tibial]]'' ''[[#apophysis|apophysis]]'' on the male ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalp]]''; also just called the tibial apophysis
{{anchor|cephalic region}}'''Cephalic region''': The front part of the ''[[#cephalothorax|cephalothorax]]'', separated from the thoracic region by the ''[[#cervical groove|cervical groove]]''{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|pp=14–15}}
{{anchor|cephalothorax}}{{anchor|prosoma}}'''Cephalothorax''' or '''prosoma''': One of the two main body parts ([[tagma (biology)|tagmata]]), located towards the [[anterior]] end, composed of the head (''[[#cephalic region|cephalic region]]'' or caput) and the thorax (thoracic region), the two regions being separated by the ''[[#cervical groove|cervical groove]]''; covered by the ''[[#carapace|carapace]]'' and bearing the eyes, legs, ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalps]]'' and mouthparts{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=14}}
{{anchor|cervical groove}}'''Cervical groove''': A shallow U-shaped groove, separating the ''[[#cephalic region|cephalic]]'' and thoracic regions of the ''[[#carapace|carapace]]''{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=14}}
{{anchor|chelicera}}'''Chelicera''' (plural chelicerae): One of two appendages at the front of the ''[[#carapace|carapace]]'', made up of basal portion, the ''[[#paturon|paturon]]'', and the ''[[#fang|fang]]'';{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|pp=15, 18}} sometimes called the jaw; see also [[Chelicerae]]
{{anchor|cheliceral furrow}}'''Cheliceral furrow''': A shallow groove on the basal portion of a ''[[#chelicera|chelicera]]'' accommodating the ''[[#fang|fang]]'', usually having teeth on its margins{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=15}}
Claw → ''[[#tarsal claw|tarsal claw]]''
{{anchor|claw tuft}}'''Claw tuft''': A dense group of hairs or bristles (setae) underneath the paired ''[[#tarsal claw|tarsal claws]]'', usually well developed in hunting spiders{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=15}}
{{anchor|clypeus}}'''Clypeus''': The area of the ''[[#carapace|carapace]]'' between the anterior (frontmost) eyes and the anterior edge of the carapace{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=15}}
{{anchor|colulus}}'''Colulus''': A short protuberance in the middle of the underside of the ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]'' in front of the ''[[#spinneret|spinnerets]]'', considered to be a modification of the ''[[#cribellum|cribellum]]''{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=15}}
Conductor → ''[[#palpal bulb|palpal bulb]]''
{{anchor|copulatory opening}}'''Copulatory opening''': An opening in the ventral ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]'' of female spiders; in [[Entelegynae|entelegyne]] spiders, a double opening in the ''[[#epigyne|epigyne]]'' through which the ''[[#embolus|embolus]]'' is inserted; in [[Haplogynae|haplogyne]] spiders, a single opening through which male ''[[#palpal bulb|palpal bulb]]'' is inserted{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=15}}
Coxa → ''[[#segments|segments]]''
{{anchor|cribellum}}'''Cribellum''': A sieve-like plate in front of the ''[[spinneret|spinnerets]]'', used in conjunction with the ''[[#calamistrum|calamistrum]]''; spiders with a cribellum are called '''cribellate''', those without '''ecribellate''';{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|pp=14–15}} see also [[Cribellum]]
{{anchor|cymbium}}'''Cymbium''' (plural cymbia): The end part of the ''[[#tarsus|tarsus]]'' of the ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalp]]'' in a mature male, usually hollowed out and bearing the ''[[#palpal bulb|palpal bulb]]''{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=15}}
===D=== {{anchor|dionychous}}'''Dionychous''': With two ''[[#tarsal claw|claws]]'' on the ''[[#tarsus|tarsus]]'' of each leg;{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=15}} a feature of spiders in the clade [[Dionycha]]
Dorsal groove → ''[[#fovea|fovea]]''
{{anchor|dorsum}}'''Dorsum''': The upper (dorsal) portion or surface of the body or ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]''; → ''[[#ventrum|ventrum]]''
===E=== Ecribellate → ''[[#cribellum|cribellum]]''
Embolus → ''[[#palpal bulb|palpal bulb]]''
Endite → ''[[#maxilla|maxilla]]''
{{anchor|entelegyne}}'''Entelegyne''': A spider whose female has an ''[[#epigyne|epigyne]]'' and separate ducts leading to ''[[#spermatheca|spermathecae]]'' for sperm storage and to the uterus for fertilization,{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=15}} creating a "flow-through" system; → ''[[#haplogyne|haplogyne]]''
{{anchor|epigastric furrow}}'''Epigastric furrow''': A transverse slit towards the front (anterior) of underside of the ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]''; the front pair of ''[[#book lungs|book lungs]]'' open at the edge of this furrow as do the genital openings (''[[#gonopore|gonopores]]''){{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=17}}
{{anchor|epigyne}}{{anchor|epigynum}}'''Epigyne''' or '''epigynum''' (plural epigynes): A hardened plate on the underside of the female ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]'' in which the ''[[#copulatory opening|copulatory openings]]'' are located; only fully developed in mature females of ''[[#entelegyne|entelegyne]]'' spiders;{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=15}} see also [[Epigyne]]
===F=== {{anchor|fang}}'''Fang''': The final hinged part of the ''[[#chelicera|chelicera]]'', normally folded down into a groove in the basal part of the chelicera; venom is injected via an opening near the tip of the fang{{sfnp|Foelix|2011|p=21}}
Femur → ''[[#segments|segments]]''
{{anchor|fertilization duct}}'''Fertilization duct''': A duct in female ''[[#entelegyne|entelegyne]]'' spiders leading from the ''[[spermatheca|spermathecae]]'' to the uterus{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=17}}
[[File:Larinioides_cornutus_2006-07-05.jpg|thumb|right|''Larinioides cornutus'' spider showing folium on abdomen]] {{anchor|folium}}'''Folium''': A broad leaf-like marking along the medial line of the top of the ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]''
{{anchor|fovea}}'''Fovea''' (also called '''thoracic furrow''' or '''dorsal groove'''): A depression or pit in the centre of the ''[[#carapace|carapace]]'' of a spider marking an inward projection of the exoskeleton to which stomach muscles are attached{{sfnp|Roberts|1995|pp=13–14}}{{sfnp|Foelix|2011|pp=17–18}}
===G=== Gnathocoxa → ''[[#maxilla|maxilla]]''
{{anchor|gonopore}}'''Gonopore''': The genital opening; located in the [[#epigastric furrow|epigastric furrow]]; see also [[Gonopore]]
===H=== Haematodocha → ''[[#palpal bulb|palpal bulb]]''
{{anchor|haplogyne}}'''Haplogyne''': A spider whose female lacks an ''[[#epigyne|epigyne]]'' and in which the same ducts are used to transport sperm to the uterus and to the ''[[#spermatheca|spermathecae]]'';{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=16}} → ''[[#entelegyne|entelegyne]]''
{{anchor|heart mark}}'''Heart mark''': A narrow marking along the top of the ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]'' roughly corresponding to the location of the heart
{{anchor|I}}{{anchor|J}}{{anchor|K}}
===L=== {{anchor|labio-sternum mound}}'''Labio-sternum mound''': A mound separating the ''[[#labium|labium]]'' from the ''[[#sternum|sternum]]'', found in found in some [[tarantula]]s, where it can be a diagnostic feature{{sfnp|Smith|1990}}
{{anchor|labium}}'''Labium''' (plural labia): A hardened plate (sclerite) between the ''[[#maxilla|maxillae]]'' at the front of the ''[[#sternum|sternum]]'';{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=17}} see also [[Arthropod mouthparts#Labium|Arthropod mouthparts: Labium]]
{{anchor|labrum}}'''Labrum''' (plural labra): A component (the "upper lip") of the mouthparts, concealed by the ''[[#chelicera|chelicerae]]'';{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=17}} see also [[Arthropod mouthparts#Labium|Arthropod mouthparts: Labrum]]
{{anchor|lateral}}'''Lateral''' (applied to appendages): Viewed from above or below, the sides of the leg or ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalp]]'', i.e. the surfaces parallel to the line of sight; → ''[[#prolateral|prolateral]]'', ''[[#retrolateral|retrolateral]]''
===M=== {{anchor|main eye}}'''Main eye''': one of the two anterior median eyes (AME) that have the light-detecting units (rhabdomeres) pointing towards the source; particularly enlarged in the families [[Salticidae]] and [[Thomisidae]];{{sfnp|Foelix|2011|pp=102–103}} → ''[[#secondary eye|secondary eye]]''
{{anchor|maxilla}}{{anchor|endite}}{{anchor|gnathocoxa}}'''Maxilla''' (also called '''endite''' or '''gnathocoxa'''): Modified ''[[#coxa|coxa]]'' of the ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalp]]'', used in feeding;{{sfnp|Foelix|2011|pp=17–18}}{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=15}} not the structure called by this name in other arthropods, for which see [[Maxilla (arthropod mouthpart)]]
Metatarsus → ''[[#segments|segments]]''
{{anchor|N}}
===O=== Opisthosoma → ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]''
===P=== Palp → ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalp]]''
[[File:Araneae palpal bulb diagram en.png|thumb|upright=1.5|Highly simplified and stylized diagram of the main parts of an inflated palpal bulb, based loosely on Coddington (1990)<ref name=Codd90>{{cite journal |last=Coddington |first=J.A. |year=1990 |title=Ontogeny and homology in the male palpus of orb-weaving spiders and their relatives, with comments on phylogeny (Araneoclada: Araneoidea, Deinopoidea) |journal=Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology |volume=496 |pp=1–52 |postscript=. Figs 5–8}}</ref>]]
{{anchor|palpal bulb}}{{anchor|bulbus}}{{anchor|palpal organ}}'''Palpal bulb''' (also called '''bulbus''', '''palpal organ''', genital bulb): The copulatory organ of the male spider, carried on the modified last segment of the ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalp]]'', used to transfer sperm to the female;{{sfnp|Foelix|2011|pp=226–227}} see also [[Palpal bulb]]
:{{anchor|conductor}}'''Conductor''': A part of the palpal bulb that accompanies and supports the embolus{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=15}}
:{{anchor|embolus}}'''Embolus''': The final part of the palpal bulb containing the end of the sperm duct, usually thin, sharp-tipped and strongly hardened (sclerotized){{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=15}}
:{{anchor|haematodocha}}'''Haematodocha''' (plural haematodochae): A membranous, inflatable part of the palpal bulb{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=17}}
:{{anchor|subtegulum}}'''Subtegulum''': A hardened part of the palpal bulb nearer its base than the tegulum
:{{anchor|tegulum}}'''Tegulum''': The main hardened part of the palpal bulb
{{anchor|paracymbium}}'''Paracymbium''': An outgrowth of the ''[[#cymbium|cymbium]]'' on the male ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalp]]''{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|pp=18–19}}
Patella → ''[[#segments|segments]]''
{{anchor|paturon}}'''Paturon''': The basal segment of a ''[[#chelicera|chelicera]]'' to which the ''[[#fang|fang]]'' connects{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=18}}
{{anchor|pedicel}}'''Pedicel''': The narrow connection between the ''[[#cephalothorax|cephalothorax]]'' and ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]''{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=18}}
{{anchor|pedipalp}}'''Pedipalp''' (plural pedipalps or pedipalpi; also called just palp): The second appendage of the ''[[#cephalothorax|cephalothorax]]'' in front of the first leg; bears the ''[[#palpal bulb|palpal bulb]]'' in male spiders;{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=17}} → ''[[#segments|segments]]''
{{anchor|plumose}}'''Plumose''' setae are hairs having outgrowths or appendages on two sides, giving a feather-like appearance; the appendages vary in number, size and arrangement<ref name=ZakhOvts15>{{Citation |last1=Zakharov |first1=Boris |last2=Ovtsharenko |first2=Vladimir |date=2015 |title=The covering setae of ground spiders (Araneae: Gnaphosidae) |journal=Arachnologische Mitteilungen 49 |volume=49 |pages=34–46 |url=http://www.european-arachnology.org/wdp/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/AM49_34-46_Zakharov2.pdf |accessdate=2017-09-28 |lastauthoramp=yes }}</ref>
{{anchor|pluridentate}}'''Pluridentate''': Having multiple teeth
{{anchor|procurved}}'''Procurved''': Used to describe a structure which is curved in such a way that the outer edges are in front of the central part;{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=18}} opposite ''[[#recurved|recurved]]''
{{anchor|prolateral}}'''Prolateral''': Viewed from above or below, the side of a leg or ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalp]]'' nearest the mouth, i.e. the side facing forward
Prosoma → ''[[#cephalothorax|cephalothorax]]''
{{anchor|Q}}
===R=== {{anchor|rastellum}}'''Rastellum''' (plural rastella): An often rake-like structure at end of the ''[[#chelicera|chelicera]]'' in [[Mygalomorphae|mygalomorph]] spiders; used in burrowing{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=18}}
Receptaculum (plural receptacula) → ''[[#spermatheca|spermatheca]]''
{{anchor|recurved}}'''Recurved''': used to describe a structure which is curved in such a way that the outer edges are behind the central part;{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=18}} opposite ''[[#procurved|procurved]]''
{{anchor|retrolateral}}'''Retrolateral''': Viewed from above or below, the side of a leg or ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalp]]'' furthest from the mouth, i.e. the side facing backwards
{{anchor|RTA}}'''Retrolateral tibial apophysis''': A backward-facing projection on the tibia of the male ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalp]]''
===S=== {{anchor|scopula}}'''Scopula''' (plural scopulae): A brush of hairs (setae); called a ''[[#claw tuft|claw tuft]]'' when on the end of the foot, where it improves adhesion{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=18}}{{sfnp|Foelix|2011|p=27}}
{{anchor|scutum}}'''Scutum''' (plural scuta): A hardened (sclerotized) plate on the ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]'' of some spiders
{{anchor|secondary eye}}'''Secondary eye''': An eye belonging to the three pairs – anterior lateral eyes (ALE), posterior median eyes (PME) and posterior lateral eyes (PLE) – that are primarily movement detectors and have the light-detecting units (rhabdomeres) pointing away from the source;{{sfnp|Foelix|2011|pp=103–104}} → ''[[#main eye|main eye]]'' [[File:Spider external anatomy appendages en.png|thumb|upright=1.25|Pedipalp and leg of a female spider from the underside; the coxa of the pedipalp is heavily modified to form the maxilla]]
{{anchor|segments}}'''Segments''' or articles of the legs and ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalps]]'':
:{{anchor|coxa}}'''Coxa''' (plural coxae): First leg segment, between body and trochanter; the coxa of the ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalp]]'' is heavily modified to form the ''[[#maxilla|maxilla]]'' or endite
:{{anchor|trochanter}}'''Trochanter''': Second leg segment, between coxa and femur
:{{anchor|femur}}'''Femur''' (plural femora): Third leg segment, between trochanter and tibia
:{{anchor|patella}}'''Patella''' (plural patellae): Fourth leg segment, between femur and tibia
:{{anchor|tibia}}'''Tibia''' (plural tibiae): Fifth leg segment, between patella and metatarsus
:{{anchor|metatarsus}}'''Metatarsus''' (plural metatarsi; also called basitarsus): Sixth leg segment, between tibia and tarsus; absent in the ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalp]]''
:{{anchor|tarsus}}'''Tarsus''' (plural tarsi; also called telotarsus): Seventh (last) leg segment, after the metatarsus
{{anchor|seta}}'''Seta''' (plural setae): A bristle;{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=18}} spiders have a variety of hair-like structures of increasing size that are referred to as hairs, bristles (setae) or ''[[#spine|spines]]''{{sfnp|Foelix|2011|pp=84–101}}
{{anchor|sigillum}}'''Sigillum''' (plural sigilla): A circular indentation on the outside of the spider, showing where an internal muscle is attached;{{sfnp|Foelix|2011|pp=41, 43}} particularly on the ''[[#sternum|sternum]]'' in some [[Mygalomorphae]] and on the ''[[#dorsum|dorsum]]'' in some [[Araneomorphae]]{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=18}}
{{anchor|sperm duct}}'''Sperm duct''': A duct in the male ''[[#palpal bulb|palpal bulb]]'' used to store sperm{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=18}}
{{anchor|spermatheca}}{{anchor|receptulacum}}'''Spermatheca''' (plural spermathecae; also called '''receptulacum''', receptulacum seminis): A structure in the ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]'' of female spiders used to store sperm after insemination and before fertilization;{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=18}} see also [[Spermatheca]]
{{anchor|spigot}}'''Spigot''': A small pointed or cylindrical structure at the tip of a ''[[#spinneret|spinneret]]'' from which silk emerges{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=18}}
{{anchor|spine}}'''Spine''': A pointed, rigid structure on body and legs, usually with a basal joint;{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=19}} spiders have a variety of hair-like structures of increasing size that are referred to as hairs, bristles (setae) or spines{{sfnp|Foelix|2011|pp=84–101}}
{{anchor|spinneret}}'''Spinneret''': An appendage borne on the ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]'', typically one of six arranged in three pairs, anterior, median and posterior; silk emerges from small ''[[#spigot|spigots]]'' on the spinnerets;{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=19}} see also [[Spinneret]]
{{anchor|sternum}}'''Sternum''': The lower (ventral) portion of the ''[[#cephalothorax|cephalothorax]]''
{{anchor|stridulating organ}}'''Stridulating organ''': A series of thin ridges on a hardened part of the body; rubbing this with a matching series of short, stiff bristles (setae) elsewhere on the body creates a sound{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=19}}
Subtegulum → ''[[#palpal bulb|palpal bulb]]''
===T=== {{anchor|tapetum}}'''Tapetum''' (plural tapeta): A light-reflecting layer in a ''[[#secondary eye|secondary eye]]'' making the eye appear pale{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=19}}
{{anchor|tarsal claw}}'''Tarsal claw''' (claw): One of a set of claws at the tip of the ''[[#tarsus|tarsus]]''; there may be a single pair, often concealed in a ''[[#claw tuft|claw tuft]]'', or an additional third central claw, much smaller than the other two{{sfnp|Saaristo|2010|p=19}}
Tarsus → ''[[#segments|segments]]''
Tegulum → ''[[#palpal bulb|palpal bulb]]''
Thoracic furrow → ''[[#fovea|fovea]]''
Tibia → ''[[#segments|segments]]''
{{anchor|trichobothrium}}'''Trichobothrium''' (plural trichobothria): A slender hair-like structure of variable length on the legs and ''[[#pedipalp|pedipalps]]'', arising from a special socket; used to detect air movements, including sounds;{{sfnp|Foelix|2011|pp=89–92}} → ''[[#seta|seta]]'', ''[[#spine|spine]]''
Trochanter → ''[[#segments|segments]]''
===U=== {{anchor|unidentate}}'''Unidentate''': Having a single tooth
{{anchor|W}}{{anchor|X}}{{anchor|Y}}{{anchor|Z}}
===V=== {{anchor|ventrum}}'''Venter''' (or '''ventrum'''): The lower (ventral) portion or surface of the body or ''[[#abdomen|abdomen]]''; → ''[[#dorsum|dorsum]]''
==Abbreviations== Some abbreviations commonly found in descriptions of spider anatomy include:{{citation needed|date=February 2016}}
*{{anchor|ALE}}'''ALE''': anterior lateral eyes *{{anchor|ALS}}'''ALS''': anterior lateral spinnerets *{{anchor|AME}}'''AME''': anterior median eyes *{{anchor|DTA}}'''DTA''': dorsal tegular apophysis *{{anchor|DTiA}}'''DTiA''': dorsal tibial apophysis *{{anchor|LTA}}'''LTA''': lateral tegular apophysis *{{anchor|MOQ}}'''MOQ''': median ocular quadrangle *{{anchor|PLE}}'''PLE''': posterior lateral eyes *{{anchor|PLS}}'''PLS''': posterior lateral spinnerets *{{anchor|PME}}'''PME''': posterior median eyes *{{anchor|PMS}}'''PMS''': posterior median spinnerets *{{anchor|RCF}}'''RCF''': retrolateral cymbial fold *{{anchor|RTA}}'''RTA''': retrolateral tibial apophysis *{{anchor|VTA}}'''VTA''': ventral tegular apophysis *{{anchor|VTiA}}'''VTiA''': ventral tibial apophysis
