{{Infobox scientist |name=Heinrich Friese |image=<!--(filename only)--> |image_size= |caption= |birth_date=4 May 1860 |birth_place=[[Schwerin]] |death_date={{d-da|8 September 1948|4 May 1860}} |death_place=Schwerin |residence= |citizenship= |nationality=German |ethnicity= |fields=[[Entomology]] and [[biology]] |workplaces= |alma_mater= |doctoral_advisor= |academic_advisors= |doctoral_students=[[Adolpho Ducke]] |notable_students= |known_for= |author_abbrev_bot= |author_abbrev_zoo=H. Friese |influences= |influenced= |awards= |signature=<!--(filename only)--> |footnotes=}} '''Heinrich Friese''' (Heinrich Friedrich August Karl Ludwig Friese, was born on 4 May, 1860 in [[Schwerin]], and died 8 September, 1948 in Schwerin) was a German [[biology|biologist]] and [[entomologist]], specialist of [[bee]]s.<ref>[http://www.mapress.com/zootaxa/2008/f/z01833p118f.pdf Heinrich Friese (1860–1948): Names proposed and notes on a pioneer [[melittology|melittologist]](Hymenoptera, Anthophila). Claus Rasmussen and John S. Ascher, Zootaxa, 2008]</ref> ==Tributes== The bee genus ''[[Eufriesea]]'' is named after him. ==References== {{Reflist}} ==External links== {{wikispecies}} * {{Internet Archive author |sname=Heinrich Friese |sopt=t}} * {{commons cat inline}} * [http://www.culturaapicola.com.ar/wiki/index.php/Heinrich_Friese Heinrich Friese on www.culturaapicola.com wiki (Spanish)] * [http://mecklenburg-natur.de/html/heinrich_friese.html Heinrich Friese on mecklenburg-natur.de (German)]
