'''Rhondda Elizabeth Jones''' was the first Professor of Zoology and the first female professor at [[James Cook University]], and served as Deputy [[Vice-Chancellor]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.jcu.edu.au/school/tbiol/zoology/staff/jones.htm |title=Professor Rhondda Jones |accessdate=2008-02-17 |work=[[James Cook University]] }}</ref> Professor Jones was previously the Chair of the Academic Board of James Cook University.

