{{Zoologist-stub}}

'''Roger A. Beaver''' is a [[biologist]] who has worked at [[University College of North Wales]],<ref>{{cite book |title=Mato Grosso, last virgin land |last=Smith |first=Anthony |year=1971 |publisher=[[Penguin Group|Michael Joseph]] |oclc=191973258 |page=284 }}</ref> [[Chiang Mai University]],<ref>{{cite journal |last=Beaver |first=R. A. |date=June 1974 |title=Intraspecific Competition among Bark Beetle Larvae (Coleoptera: Scolytidae) |journal=Journal of Animal Ecology |publisher=[[British Ecological Society]] |volume=43 |issue=2 |pages=455–467 |jstor=3376 |doi=10.2307/3376 }}</ref> the [[University of Zambia]]<ref>{{cite journal |last=Beaver |first=R. A. |date=September 1979 |title=Host specificity of temperate and tropical animals |journal=[[Nature (journal)|Nature]] |volume=281 |pages=139–141 |doi=10.1038/281139a0 |issue=5727}}</ref> and the [[University of the South Pacific]].<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1163/187631286X00189 |last=Beaver |first=R. A. |year=1986 |title=The taxonomy, mycangia and biology of Hypothenemus curtipennis (Schedl), the first known cryphaline ambrosia beetle (Coleoptera: Scolytidae)  |journal=Insect Systematics & Evolution |publisher=[[Brill Publishers|Brill]] |volume=17 |issue=1 |pages=131–135 |issn=1399-560X |url=http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/brill/ise/1986/00000017/00000001/art00010?crawler=true }}</ref> He has published several important papers on [[Nepenthes infauna|''Nepenthes'' infauna]], including "Fauna and food webs of pitcher plants in West Malaysia" (1979), "The communities living in ''Nepenthes'' pitcher plants: fauna and food webs" (1983), and "Geographical variation in food web structure in ''Nepenthes'' pitcher plants" (1985). The species ''[[Cryptoxilos beaveri]]'' was named in his honour.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Shaw |first=Scott Richard |author2=Jocelyn A. Berry  |date=December 2005 |title= Two new ''Cryptoxilos'' species (Hymenoptera : Braconidae : Euphorinae) from New Zealand and Fiji parasitising adult Scolytinae (Coleoptera) |journal=Invertebrate Systematics |publisher=[[CSIRO Publishing]] |volume=19 |issue=5 |pages=371–381 |doi=10.1071/IS05021 }}</ref>

